summary: This is a search warrant issued by the U.S. District Court for the Southern District of New York authorizing the search of a multi-story single-family residence in New York, New York, related to violations of sex trafficking of minors and conspiracy. The warrant lists specific items to be seized, including taxidermied dogs, massage tables, busts of female torsos, photos of nude women, sex paraphernalia, and a binder labeled 'NI Girls'.

persons.name: Barbara Moses

events.title: Issuance of Search Warrant
events.description: A search warrant was issued by Magistrate Judge Barbara Moses authorizing the search of a multi-story single-family residence in New York, NY, for evidence related to sex trafficking of minors and conspiracy.

locations: Multi-story single-family residence at unspecified address in New York, NY
keyFacts: The search warrant targets a residence in New York, NY, for evidence of violations of Title 18, U.S. Code, Sections 1591 (sex trafficking of minors) and 371 (conspiracy).
Specific items to be seized include taxidermied dogs, massage tables and paraphernalia, busts of female torsos, photos of nude women in a 'Massage Room', sex toys, and a binder labeled 'NI Girls'.
The warrant was issued by Magistrate Judge Barbara Moses and must be executed by May 7, 2019, with authorization for delayed notice to the person whose property is searched.
